<paragraph box="[96,1370,427,569]" pageId="3" pageNumber="7" type="mainText">
Note: This species resembles 
<taxonomicName class="Bryopsida" family="Dicranaceae" genus="Campylopus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Dicranales" pageId="3" pageNumber="7" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="pilifer">C. pilifer</taxonomicName>
in the involute upper lamina, smooth or only slightly senate. It is different in the distinctly coloured and inflated alar cells and the more elongate and incrassate upper laminal Cells.
</paragraph>
